.TH "memory_map_top_down" 9 "memory_map_top_down" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
memory_map_top_down \- Map [map_start, map_end) top down
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" memory_map_top_down
.BI "(unsigned long map_start "  ","
.BI "unsigned long map_end "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "map_start" 12
start address of the target memory range
.IP "map_end" 12
end address of the target memory range
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function will setup direct mapping for memory range
[map_start, map_end) in top-down. That said, the page tables
will be allocated at the end of the memory, and we map the
memory in top-down.
